---
title: Speedy Vietnamese Lemongrass Stir Fry with Roaming Roosters Steak
description: Just like a rooster, these steaks are super quick! Known for being super tender, these flank steaks are served with steamy jasmine rice and chilli with white wine vinegar to give it that authentic hot and sour flavour combination. To make sure you are getting at least some of your five a day, we have added some fresh green beans, spring onions and red peppers!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5594160df8b25e93068b4567.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/5594160df8b25e93068b4567.pdf
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Vietnamese
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 571 kcal
  fat: 10 g
  saturated fat: 4 g
  carbohydrates: 82 g
  protein: 36 g
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/speedy-vietnamese-lemongrass-stir-fry-5594160df8b25e93068b4567
---

Boil @water{700%ml} with @salt{1/4%tsp} in a #pot. Once it comes to a boil add the @Basmati Rice{2} and turn the heat to it's lowest setting. Put a tight fitting lid on top and cook for ~{10%mins}. Remove from the heat and leave to rest for another ~{10%mins}. Do not peek under the lid until 20 mins is up or the rice won't cook!

Meanwhile, chop your @Spring Onion{4}(chopped widthways into very thin discs) and separate the white and green parts. Chop the @Green Beans{2}(chopped widthways into 3cm pieces). Remove the core from the @Red Pepper{2} and chop it into roughly 2cm chunks. Finely chop the @Red Chilli{1} and peel and finely chop the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and finely chopped).

Chop the tough base off the @Lemongrass{1} and peel a couple of the outer layers. Take the bit in the middle and whack it with something heavy to break it up a bit (and release that awesome lemony smell). Very, very finely chop it for later.

> It's really important you chop, chop, chop the lemongrass to make sure it cooks perfectly.

Now slice the @Flank Steak{600%g} widthways into wafer thin strips. Toss the strips in a #bowl together with @salt{1/4%tsp}, a good pinch of @ground black pepper{pinch} and the @Cornflour{3%tsp}.

Heat @oil{1%tbsp} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on high heat. Once the oil is nice and hot, gently place the beef strips into the pan and brown them off for ~{2%mins}. Remove from the pan and keep to the side.

In the (now empty) #frying pan, heat @oil{2%tsp} and turn the heat to medium-high. Add the garlic, lemongrass, chilli and the whites of the spring onions and cook for ~{2%mins}. Now add the beans and red pepper, and cook for ~{5%mins} (tossing them constantly).

Throw in the @Soy Sauce{4%tsp}, @White Wine Vinegar{2%tsp}, @?sugar{1%tsp} and @water{3%tbsp} together with the beef and toss the pan for another ~{2%mins}.

Serve your lemongrass stir fry on top of the rice with a sprinkle of spring onions and BOOM, you're done!